text: The Karesuando Church () is a wooden church building in Karesuando in Sweden. It belongs to the Karesuando Parish of the Church of Sweden. It was inaugurated on 3 December 1905 by Bishop Olof Bergqvist of the Diocese of Lule√•. It then replaced an older church. The church is the northernmost church in Sweden. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Wooden churches
